<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - GASKET SEALANT
        - INSTALLING THE SEALANT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1303304" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALLING THE SEALANT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303311">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the mounting surfaces with a chlorinated solvent such as Loctite Safety Solvent or
                equivalent.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Apply the sealant in a 3 mm (1/8 inch) bead. If too much sealant is used, the sealant that extends
                    over the edges can break off and plug the oil passages.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite RTV Sealant #5699 with a sealant dispenser to one surface. Apply the sealant
                in a continuous pattern with a 3 mm (1/8 inch) bead. Make sure the bead encircles any fastener holes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303311" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303311.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Installing the Sealant</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
